answers.body_markdown:
You have no Query for getting specific `Event` with its `id`. Your &quot;events&quot; query does not accept any args and is expected to return an array of *Events*.

    type RootQuery {
       events: [Event!]!
    }

See the following example from the [docs][1]

&gt;     type Query {
&gt;       human(id: ID!): Human
&gt;     }
&gt;     
&gt;     type Human {
&gt;       name: String
&gt;       appearsIn: [Episode]
&gt;       starships: [Starship]
&gt;     }
&gt;     
&gt;     enum Episode {
&gt;       NEWHOPE
&gt;       EMPIRE
&gt;       JEDI
&gt;     }
&gt;     
&gt;     type Starship {
&gt;       name: String
&gt;     }
&gt; 
&gt; In order to describe what happens when a query is executed, let&#39;s use
&gt; an example to walk through.
&gt; 
&gt;     {
&gt;       human(id: 1002) {
&gt;         name
&gt;         appearsIn
&gt;         starships {
&gt;           name
&gt;         }
&gt;       }
&gt;     }
&gt;     
&gt; Result
&gt; 
&gt;     {
&gt;       &quot;data&quot;: {
&gt;         &quot;human&quot;: {
&gt;           &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Han Solo&quot;,
&gt;           &quot;appearsIn&quot;: [
&gt;             &quot;NEWHOPE&quot;,
&gt;             &quot;EMPIRE&quot;,
&gt;             &quot;JEDI&quot;
&gt;           ],
&gt;           &quot;starships&quot;: [
&gt;             {
&gt;               &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Millenium Falcon&quot;
&gt;             },
&gt;             {
&gt;               &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Imperial shuttle&quot;
&gt;             }
&gt;           ]
&gt;         }
&gt;       }
&gt;     }


Take note of the example

    type Query {
      human(id: ID!): Human
    }

In your case, you will have to make something like that from above:

    type Event{
      event(id: ID!): Event
    }

  [1]: https://graphql.org/learn/execution/

